  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (6676e81 2023-08-22T00:28:15.086036000Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforget test\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Apple Silicon)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI have a contract that interacts with Optimism's `crossDomainMessenger` setup, the message gets sent from L1 to L2 and then the `L2CrossDomainMessenger` calls a specified contract on L2 with some message payload, this call is supposed to revert in the test, it reverts when I run forge test and the error appears in the execution trace. However, when I `vm.expectRevert()` that error, forge test complains that: \r\n\r\n```\r\n[FAIL. Reason: Call did not revert as expected. ...]\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe test in question can be found [here](https://github.com/worldcoin/world-id-state-bridge/blob/a8d3952eb8949c28982216ff90347aaba6b0b5ea/src/test/OpWorldID.t.sol#L178-L268). To replicate this error, uncomment [line 250](https://github.com/worldcoin/world-id-state-bridge/blob/a8d3952eb8949c28982216ff90347aaba6b0b5ea/src/test/OpWorldID.t.sol#L250) and run \r\n\r\n```bash\r\nforge test --match-test test_receiveRoot_reverts_CannotOverwriteRoot -vvvvv \r\n```\r\n\r\nThanks for any help and don't hesitate to DM me on [TG](t.me/dcbuild3r) or tag me in this issue.",
